[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating metadata and file issues**\n\nI notice there's an untracked file that might not need further changes. To avoid failures with ClassNotFound, I could try a custom resolve, but then might hit a MissingReflection issue unless metadata is available. If Forge adds the metadata, perhaps the custom resolve will work. \n\nAlso, JVM agent recording serialization might help with metadata. The question of which version is better remains because if real metadata is expected, including the class might be better, while default resolution is backed by registration for native image. But the developer advises against editing metadata, which complicates things.\n\n**Assessing dynamic access coverage**\n\nI need to consider whether an active class needs coverage after the agent and what happens without metadata. I'm thinking about dynamic-access coverage that might not be impacted by native failures. It seems to involve reading dynamic-access calls from static instrumentation during native runs, which returns false if not reachable. If native fails beforehand, there's no coverage. Perhaps external Forge can add metadata during dynamic access. So, dynamic-access coverage checks if tests reach metadata call sites during native-image compilation.\n\n**Understanding Java Serialization Issues**\n\nI'm trying to grasp what \"supported behavior through library normal public API\" means in terms of JDKDSAPublicKey. While it has public methods, there's no public factory, and its serialization relies on standard Java serialization behavior. Since it can be instantiated without a constructor, this seems like a normal construction path. I may need to supply `serialVersionUID` and `serialPersistentFields`. The ClassNotFound error indicates that \"readObject\" isn't being reached, so I might need a custom resolve to avoid this. I'll experiment with generated metadata to see if t