 helps.\n\n**Analyzing Serialization Reports**\n\nI'm looking into the coverage report after my first attempt, which returned \"none,\" while the second attempt didn't. I think this might be due to the previous descriptor replacement not using writeClassDescriptor properly. I've decided to combine the current writeClassDescriptor with a custom resolve; that shouldn't harm the JVM. If I add external metadata designating the class as serializable, it may function better. Still, I'm pondering if the default resolve would register it with Class.forName. Should I catch MissingReflection as unsupported? Maybe I'll finalize with a clearer explanation.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_075469fa47f4eac2016a10ecb3a3d0819489bc545f9c4c6548\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEOzX_X43U35053vQsWDn8-UzolS6GuZmi7rLFjwXEiNIIWCpUMc4qoJCi76RhLdSe5eLP0izqVOfYyn8BAfPW5fxY_yQB-26OhQ3xQRK-F7AHoLMa6O-Fp0R-fFkndiC_jjVDXs9SuBPOamwnRx2oZ-e1qp-SnjRTl-zOhhyQIQMeNa7vUKcY3LobmbOUS99NwctVIFk8xMR3LK6ZgBFBrjhk-EJYkzQQy8zZO5vBc37HPWDenvWCOpgv1EheQuZPbd7ro6pdO_cn4wq5Oe9QA_zg4ADlAcvU9En7OnauUbODCjyGhwId5o8FCE-fuuC8HqiklsSOCnghdMDSwRAZFs0qja2YpVi2uzHQQss5wll59IY-x7ew7jPBN85JprVDz3chnJXQUW_3-_zCxQ1hjd5pKCR3adOu3SyhLysLVbEc8dUNBg3nCR-YSo5REqxknsbzEgia9RLCI426-UpMqn4pySdwTG1oR8g7xsMZAuXOGaz05kKuEQ2mS1Ha17YO2cvpHvZvYMaqP6UuKNYwhM7Mpe7EanntI2QK9BCsoa93IrNdDcVA5BLprsCbXVrnU6sy5EPieB7baDQxBWD4BahbOPojClkPaRXGRPlE5Y93VAQIqg8JfpF7civD4k1G5c-v4DPlvZmTnRxUNxdLMoz1fECthYOqJu-rwVfCVAv85YhrHRJEzhHHo5R_NuDH3uymK8qrXxodVqQPzopcSeXyTIQ70ZjyVvnD3_3K5PELxNshJy-lzZ0vC4-sT8J-s2TU6cg3tExypxqy4XZB31FUDDF1jBlrnW_4QNxEKLCqSJiqaqiBhakkQ4oaAk6TFIQT1pKqpSdIMTREEdVt9-_f5OGuvt03DJ0d6-a9xhnqzPIvjSfEaJ7fASV80u3CS9PayZj8a782l8jFLVGeelmi6Ovsl5jh0brKS-4Sv9MqpTMDC2Ga1XLdfA9i7D3nRQGTP-_gpdA3pmVB48delDL7iTI4M2STzFzdhkjvYyoAmBqCE9902uJhUx70ki9UGle4IvCFGZOKOXiZQp9JJIrupRwzwrrhuX7eQNVP2HoMtKIDV3Mi3JRu39zax7bMql0xq1YC3rLTd52qPugEfPLzt0U7zPcuJX6OUpMhZ8jkwig4Pa9hs0dXy3sjMZNRDZ9SQ_JEj9y2omEKM6Ibf1PQPfk-Fcu5oQ-KVDmIkuNvYCWJc